Lesson 3: I was only able to do this analysis because the data and materials were open. Open data are great. But (to use a @siminevazire analogy) transparency only opens the hood. You still need to see what the engine looks like.

Second, the authors also collected people's estimates of the temperature ("What do you think the temperature is outside right now?"). This was not reported in the paper, but it is in the open data + materials. This is a plausible alternative DV.
